article.headline: Southern 69, Alcorn State 57
article.story: LORMAN, Miss. (AP) -- Alvin Mott had 21 points to lead Southern to a 69-57 victory over Alcorn State on Saturday night. Chris Alexander added 12 points and Jerrid Campbell had 11 for the first-place Jaguars (14-12, 13-3 Southwestern Athletic Conference), who have won five of six. Southern used a big first half to take control. The Jaguars shot better than 53 percent in the half, took the lead for good midway through it when Campbell's jumper made it 22-21 and led 45-32 at halftime. Alcorn State didn't get closer than seven in the second half in losing its fourth straight. Delvin Thompson led the Braves (6-19, 6-10) with 20 points, and Clif Douglass added 10. Peter Cipriano -- who entered as the SWAC's second-leading rebounder, averaging 8.1 -- nearly doubled his average with 16 against Alcorn State. Southern outrebounded the Braves 42-27.
